"a.比喻的，借喻的 【英】 adj.比喻的，借喻的( metaphoric) 【记】 来自figure(外形，象 征)+ative→象征性的 →比喻的 【例】 'A sweet temper' is a figurative expression. adj. 比喻的 = metaphorical; 文风华丽的 = ornate 【记】figure(n 外形; 轮廓; 数字vt 描绘; 象征), ative－象征性的－比喻的－比喻用得多－文风华丽的 【反】literal(adj 文字的; 照字面上的; 无夸张的) 【记】figure 图形，象征)→用图形来比喻 figurative (adj.)  late 14c., from Old French figuratif ""metaphorical,"" from Late Latin figurativus, from figurat-, past participle stem of figurare ""to form, shape,"" from figura ""a shape, form, figure"" (see figure (n.)). Of speech, language, etc., ""involving figures of speech,"" from 1845. Related: Figuratively."
